    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-09T13:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-09T13:53:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <head>96. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station in Guatemala</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d96fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79-01025A, Box 1, Folder 5. Secret; Priority; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>; RYBAT. Repeated to the
                        Director of Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-09T18:53:00+00:00">February 9, 1954,
                        1853Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>451. Re: <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 399.<note n="2" xml:id="d96fn2"
                        >Not printed. (Ibid., Box 1001, Folder 4)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In accordance with ref, request <gloss target="#t_ETA1">ETA</gloss>
                        Givloch soonest.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Prior to trip, request Givloch confer with FMBLUG to obtain <gloss
                            target="#t_JMBLUG1">JMBLUG</gloss>’s personal views on following: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>What political platform should an anti-Commie group, seeking to
                                overthrow <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss> Govt, espouse?
                                What should be announced position of such group on agrarian reform,
                                foreign capital, role of army, labor unions, nationalism,
                                etc.?</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>What political actions must an anti-Commie group, once it has
                                seized power, carry out to remain in power? What should it actually
                                do on the planks contained in its pre-coup platform?</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Above is for <persName>LINCOLN</persName> guidance prior to shaping up
                            [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]/<persName
                            corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> positive political
                        program.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_DIR1">Dir</gloss> FYI: Believe foregoing guidance helpful
                        and easily obtainable but not to be construed as any effort to bypass <gloss
                            target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
